Looking to sell this 6" O.P. serial number 8291XX.

First the good: I was going to the range recently any way so I took this along to make sure it functioned okay. I shot 6 cylinders through it, and it seems to shoot great, very pleasant to shoot, and when I paid attention it seemed to be very consistent with its shot groupings.

Now the bad: These grips are not original to this gun. They do look quite natural on it though, and show a matching level of wear. The finish has several issues with it, hopefully depicted. Mechanically, if you pull the hammer back, pull the trigger, and leave the trigger depressed, the cylinder is locked up tight. I have only noticed this happening with counter clockwise pressure, not with clockwise pressure. Underneath the left stock (hidden from view, someone has scratched CBA0193).

title: For Sale:  CNC Warrior VZ-58 + Extras
postcontent:
WILL UPLOAD MORE PICTURES THIS WEEKEND. (4/18 & 4/19)

I have a CNC Warrior VZ58 rifle for sale.  This rifle comes with a LOT of extras!  I’ve had it since 2013 and have put a lot of money and time into it.  Unfortunately I need to move onto other projects and I never shoot it.  Selling it would help me do just that.

I changed out the composite wood stock, grip and fore grip with polymer ones so I could fit optics, etc.  I also liked the tactical look on the rifle better.  I fitted it with a single point sling attachment and AR stock tube kit so I could use an adjustable stock (includes Magpul STR stock in black).  

Once the stock and extra kit were fitted I wanted to get more into suppression.  Since the VZ has a thinner barrel and odd thread type I had to have the barrel re-done.  I had it shortened and an AAC 51T muzzle device welded on at Rocky Mountain Weaponry in Colorado.  This rifle did start out as a Century Arms VZ2008.  Since the Century rifles use all Czech parts (barrel/internals/gas system) and the receiver is the only part manufactured by Century, the rifle was disassembled and the receiver was then replaced with the CNC Warrior unit (Look up CNC Warrior in North Carolina, these units are VERY sought after, have great feed ramps and excellent quality, perfect spec and very hard to find).  The rifle and all 5 magazines were all then cerakoted and reassembled.  

***NOTE***
THIS IS NOT AN AK-47/74 OR A VARIANT.  Parts, magazines, etc. are NOT compatible between the AK and VZ platforms.

WHAT’S INCLUDED:
-Original Grip
-Original Fore grip
-Original 4 mag leather mag pouch
-100% functional/working rifle

-Polymer FAB Defense fore grip with picatinny system

title: For Sale:  1860 Army Colt, silver plated with Col. name engraved
postcontent:
I have a model 1860 Army Colt, .44 caliber percussion revolver I need to sell. Its in about 65% condition. I really don't want to sell it but emergency expenses are making me. I got it in trade a few years ago and it doesn't have any sentimental value so it's the one that has to go.

The serial number on the main frame housing doesn't match the serial numbers on the trigger frame, grip strap and the barrel.

The markings on it are:
Barrel: Top Side- Address Col. SamL Colt New York US America
Right Side- There is an H with a slash below it
Left Side- Above the screw it has "GG"
Under Plunger: There is what looks like an S or a 5
Back by the cylinder nipples is a "B"
Bottom back by plunger: "S 8"
Back(where it butts by the frame): What looks like a "C" and a "2"
Cylinder:
-LTS Patent No 2634, PAT Sept 10th 1855(I believe it says 1855, but the second 5 is a little faded so I'm not 100% sure)
-G
-H
Trigger Strap:
-Back: Col. F. B. Stone, USA I362(Possibly 1362, the 1st number/letter is a bit faded)
-Bottom: Serial Number
-Top by Trigger Frame: The inspection mark is pretty faded, I think it has a "C"
Frame:
-Where cylinder butts up against the frame there is a R
- Left Side has "Colts Patent"
-Under has the serial number

There is some pitting, a bit of rust, and the silver plating has rubbed off in some areas. The wood grips are in decent shape, some nicks and scratches but overall about 90% condition. Barrel is pretty clean considering the age, and the rifling is still fully visible.
The hammer sticks sometimes, i think its because of the different frame but this is more a collectable than a daily shooter so that shouldnt be too big a deal.
Like I said, I really need cash and no reasonable offers will be turned down so make me an offer and we'll see what kind of deal we can make.
